# Copy to `INSTRUCTIONS.md` (same folder) to give every agent the same
# cross-project, machine-level instructions. One file, wired into each agent's
# native global path: ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md, ~/.codex/AGENTS.md, ~/.gemini/GEMINI.md.
#
# Project-specific rules belong in the repo (its own CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md).
# This is for things you want true everywhere, regardless of which repo or agent.
#
# A per-agent override wins: if you drop a CLAUDE.md in agents/claude/ (or
# AGENTS.md in agents/codex/, GEMINI.md in agents/gemini/), that agent uses it
# instead of this shared file.

## How I work
- Prefer small, reviewable commits. Explain *why* in the message, not just what.
- Verify before claiming done: run the build and tests, don't assume.
- Match the surrounding code's style; don't reformat unrelated lines.
- When you're unsure, ask rather than guess on anything destructive.

## Your sandbox
- You run inside a coop container — that container is your sandbox and security
  boundary. OS-level sandboxing (bubblewrap) is intentionally absent here, so a
  missing sandbox or a "bubblewrap is required" notice is expected, not a bug.
  Don't stop to investigate, work around, or report it — just carry on.
